<TITLE> Babar refused bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 5 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court on Wednesday refused former BNP state minister Lutfozzaman Babar bail in two cases related to Aug 21 grenade attack on an Awami League rally. Dhaka additional chief metropolitan magistrate Mohammed Ali Hossain Babar gave the order after hearing his petition. Jainal Abedin Mesbah, the lawyer for Babar, told bdnews24.com that he will move the Dhaka district judge's court against this decision. Babar is currently serving 17 years following his conviction in an arms case. The BNP leader is also facing charges of concealing income of around Tk 8.6 crore in 1999-2000 and 2008-2009 tax years and failing to pay the tax counted on it as a director of Master Electronics Industry Limited. Babar was remanded for 12 days in two phases in connection with the murder of former Awami League finance minister Shah A M S Kibria, on Feb 11 and on Mar 14.
